                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.001C13/87: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Governor of Texas</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moody</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Austin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-16">December 16,
                            1929</date>.<lb/>[Received 12:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your wire 14th. I feel confident that Mr. Valls will make no attempt to have a
                    warrant of arrest served on General Calles when he passes through Texas en route
                    to Mexico.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dan Moody</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
